Results.ReviewText: This is my favourite blend from Nescafé.Its dark strong & tastes so good ,like real coffee should.I buy this coffee everywhere we travel & one thing you can be sure of the quality is always excellent
Results.Title: For that perfect cup of coffee

ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear you're not a fan of the new recipe. During the recent recipe change, micro ground coffee was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! It can also leave a residue at the bottom of your cup. We've made a note of your feedback & will be passing it on to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I always chose Nescafe Gold Black as it was strong and flavoursome and almost as good as a proper filter coffee. I noticed the new jar but just thought it was a rebranding exercise and bought it as usual. I could not have been more wrong-the whole taste of the coffee has changed-it is really bitter and has a horrid and unpalatable aftertaste. Worse still it does not dissolve properly whatever I do to try to encourage it to do so and leaves a vile gloopy black sludge in the bottom of my mug. I will not be buying this product again
Results.Title: So disappointing and so not worth the bother

Results.ReviewText:
I usually buy Gold Blend but on seeing the new Gold Blend BLACK I decided to buy a jar of this on Friday and immediately opened it to make a cuppa. On opening the coffee aroma was so inviting and smelt just like freshly ground coffee.
I chose to drink it black and it was rich and strong but oh so smooth and not a trace of bitterness. It will be permanently on my shopping list from now on.
Results.Title: BLACK from Nescafe is fantastic, smooth and rich.

Photos.Caption: The Legend that is Elvis with the Legend That is Nescafe

Results.ReviewText: I first tried Nescafe Gold Black a few months back, now I am hooked and nothing comes close to the smooth unique taste that enlightens my mouth, getting up in the mornings used to be a chore now I cant wait to get up from my slumber to enjoy the taste that is Nescafe Gold Black. I wouldn't hesitate to recommend this coffee to caffeine lovers around the world !!
Results.Title: Nescafe Gold a taste to behold !

Results.ReviewText:
If you long for a journey that takes you beyond the depths of the darkest chocolate then this is the coffee for you. Instantly the aroma reaches the senses, you can taste the smell before it touches your lips. A cup of Nescafe Gold Black is like laying on a feather pillow after banging your head against the wall of coffees as you strive to find instant satisfaction within a jar.

Serving suggestion - Indulge yourself in a decedent after dinner treat. Simply make a cup of Nescafe Gold Black and pour over a good quality vanilla ice cream, dust with cinnamon or cocoa powder  - heaven
Results.Title: As dark as midnight chocolate

Results.ReviewText: Delicate, beautifully made. Can’t start my day without nescafe. The first drink i have every morning and last drink i have before go to ber. I literally can’t live without my coffee..THANKS NESCAFE☕️
Results.Title: Loving this coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made. Each of the jars still have a coloured label on the front to ensure consumers can still find them in store. We really value your feedback & will be letting the rest of the team know!

Results.ReviewText:
Firstly, this product is now hard to differentiate between the other "Gold" varieties on the shelf - they all look the same. It took me ages to find it having first thought that Black Gold had been discontinued.
Secondly, Nestle, what possessed you to add ground coffee??? If I wanted ground coffee in my instant I would buy Azera (or similar), which I don't because I don't like it. Although I appreciate that it is very finely ground, it still gives a grainy texture to the coffee - which I noticed immediately in my first cup from the new jar. It also unbalances what was a really good smooth & rich tasting coffee making it bitter, grainy and, well, not very rounded.  Overall Nestle very poor. Having been a Black Gold drinker for almost 8 years now, I will no longer be buying this.
Results.Title: "If it ain't broke don't fix it"

Results.ReviewText: There is only one thing, well two.., that I'm looking forward in the morning.... my Nescafe intense and my scramble egg... while I eat my eggs my gold coffee will rest till reach the right temperature (for me at least!) and then it's mine !!! waking me up slowly but surely... ahhh thanks buddy !!! \m/
Results.Title: the new GOLD is BLACK

Results.ReviewText: I've been through the range of Nescafe products, from the standard Gold Blend (My usual Tipple) and Nescafe Original (Not good in my opinion), to some of the fancier ranges like Nescafe Asta La Vista (or whatever it's called) ... I've always gone back to standard Gold Blend, now having tried the Black version I'm converted ... I always drink strong coffee anyway (3 or 4 tea spoons) so it's a welcome relief to have a stronger blend.  It has a good, hearty "feet up in the winter in front of a roaring fire" vibe to it, with smokey rich flavours.  It's a great everyday cup of coffee
Results.Title: Strong, Hearty coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know! It's sad to hear you're not liking the changes but we appreciate your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: Ever since you changed Blend 37 for the worse, after much searching and money spending I started to drink Gold Black. I cant believe you have done the same thing again, this time to Black Gold. Its now a tasteless cup of dusty water!! Even my wife can tell the difference and she drinks a lot less than me.  Why, why, why??? I think your consumer tests suck!! Its AWFUL!
Results.Title: You've changed it!!

ClientResponses.Response: We're really disappointed to hear this. If you don’t like the rich taste, or the micro ground coffee, you could try NESCAFÉ Crema, which has taste similar to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend, however is smoother, and does not contain micro ground coffee.

Results.ReviewText: I'm so sad that you have chosen to ruin my favourite drink. It now closely resembles a cheap supermarket brand coffee. If I wanted a "Barista style" coffee with sludge at the bottom I wouldn't be drinking Gold Blend in the first place. (Perhaps you could bring out "Gold Blend Original"???
Results.Title: You spoiled my favourite coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Hey Hilary, thank you for getting in touch with us. We've added micro ground coffee to our NESCAFÉ Gold Blend to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. It's a shame you don't enjoy the changes. We'll be making a note of your comments.

Results.ReviewText: Bought this 2weeks ago and my husband says it is tasteless needs a very heaped spoon to get any taste he normally drinks Original Nescafe or Alta Rica.  I find it watery and a little bitter and normally drink Nescafe Gold, Colombian or Alta Rica.  Very disappointed won't by again
Results.Title: What taste?

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for getting in touch & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made. We appreciate everyone's feedback & we're making a note of all comments.

Results.ReviewText: I am upset that the recipe has changed, it tastes now like the low-range supermarket own-brand coffees. It seems the granules are different, with a stiffer mouthfeel. The roasted beans add to it a bit of a burnt taste
Results.Title: Maybe a mistake, adding roasted beans

Results.ReviewText: have been using this coffee for years, probably since shortly after it came out.   Before this we drank Nescafe Gold but the Black has got so much more taste without being bitter.
Results.Title: strong but wonderful taste.

Results.ReviewText: I was on a quest for an instant coffee that could be passed  off as percolated  but without the hassle. An easy task? Oh no - it's a jungle out there - the seemingly 'obvious' ones were unpleasantly  bitter  - I'm still looking for ways of using them up. But I knew there was one for me (and my unsuspecting visitors) out there somewhere - determination paid off and Nescafe Gold Black  gets a 5* from me and satisfied guests.
Results.Title: Impress the guests

Results.ReviewText: buy this coffee all the time,enjoy my coffee strong,this blend really tickles the taste buds,and unlike normal coffee i have to have two teaspoons for a decent cup, with gold blend dark i just need one,have trouble finding it stores seem to stock it then stop and start so I usually stock up when I find it,good job I live on my own would begrufed sharing it,sorry for the spelling
Results.Title: BOLD

ClientResponses.Response: We’re always wanting to improve the product for our loyal fans! After receiving feedback, we've added roast and ground coffee to our blend, to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. Watch this video to learn more: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

Results.ReviewText: Why have you changed my coffee of choice when you changed the jar, I am 65 years old and have used Nescafe coffee all my life, I drink black coffee and switched to the black gold when it came out so quite some years ago and have always been happy with it until now, I still had several of the old jars when the new one came out wish I had more The coffee in the new jars leave a horrible powder at the bottom of you cup or mug. It seems to be a cheaper product. Not happy and will be changing my coffee. Before you changed the coffee I would have given it 5 now I would give it 0 if I could. I am not a tea drinker and drink coffee black without sugar so the flavour of the coffee is important please bring back the old black gold as it used to be before the jar change
Results.Title: Black gold

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk original Gold Blend for more years than I care to remember. Of late I found the taste has changed and become very weak and lack lustre. Gold Blend Black is a vast improvement. I use a coffee machine  regularly but find Gold Black for an instant coffee is almost as good in flavour. Rich and strong like coffee should be! It's  a winner for me
Results.Title: Full bodied

Results.ReviewText: nescafe gold is a rich strong flavour,ideal to wake up with and of an evening with a brandy or benedictine or whatever your tipple is,serve black with a measure of spirit,2 teaspoons sugar. and a layer of cream on top,pour cream over the back of a teaspoon to stop it sinking,with a dark choclate on the side:-)I find this coffee goes a long way due to the strength,its a touch of luxury and visitors will think is fresh coffee if you hide the jar and boil up a tiny amount in water to pervade the air before they come :-)
Results.Title: strikingly strong

Results.ReviewText: I'm a massive coffee snob, for my sins, I really don't like instant coffee and unfortunately we have no decent coffee maker at work, but when I tried Nescafe GOLD Black I was amazed at the taste of the blend. The taste wasn't the usually 'irony' taste I get off instant coffee, it was a rich and deep roasted taste
Results.Title: Fusspot

Results.ReviewText: I was on holiday in the west of Ireland for a few weeks and with the weather changing so often it was nice to have the tasty, perfect and dependable Nestle Gold Blend coffee every morning, there is nothing like watching the sun rise in Ireland with the best cup of instant coffee in your hand.
Results.Title: just so dependable and consistently good

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking Nescafe Gold Black for some years now and loved it. Recently the product changed, I think. The packaging certainly has and I now find that it is not as good. There is normally some powdery residue left in the cup and if you do not 'swill' the coffee around as the level drops, the residue can be quite a bit. It is still a nice cup of coffee, but not, in my opinion, as nice as it was prior to the recent change.
Results.Title: Black Has Changed

Results.Title: awful

Results.ReviewText: I thought I'd try Nescafe Gold Black, from pouring on the hot water the fullness of the aroma filled the kitchen,so much so my wife joined me in a cup after catching the aroma!!  Could not wait to try this new blend from a quality name, so I took a sip on the way to my favourite chair, upon doing so I was instantly reminded and transported to a barista in Italy - its flavour overwhelmes your environment capivating you until the last drop - it's sheer endulgance that your worth.
Results.Title: Ultimate luxury

Results.ReviewText: I bought this a a few months ago it so nice the coffee great for when you need that extra kick
Results.Title: Great taste

Results.ReviewText: Normally when buying a instant dark coffee i find them to be way too bitter and taste quite dry, where as when i bought Nescafe Gold Black, it was so rich,dark and warming and i got no bitter aftertaste. For the price of about £8 it is definitely worth it. You get a great amount for the price and it lasts you quite a while. One thing i will say about it is, if you want it at its best, then make sure you have it hot... Like most coffees it doesn't taste as good cold.
Results.Title: Great taste, Very Warming

Results.ReviewText: I always keep a jar of Black Gold Coffee for after dinner with friends, when we want to enjoy a dark rich black coffee.  A couple of years ago, I bought an popular coffee machine.  After using it a couple of times, some friends - who had been for a dinner party said, "don't mean to be rude, but have you changed your coffee? - this isn't as good as the one we're used to here", gave the machine to Charity Shop & back to Black Gold, think that said it all.
Results.Title: our "Grown-up After Dinner Coffee"

Results.ReviewText: I normally drink freshly ground and brewed coffee but have been very busy lately and have been foregoing my coffee when I just haven't had the time for making my usual brew. However, fed up of my caffeine withdrawals, my sister introduced me to Nescafé Gold Black and my life has been revolutionized! I can now have a lovely rich dark coffee in a fraction of the time and am a much better person with my caffeine hit in the mornings :-) Thank you Nescafé
Results.Title: Great coffee

Results.ReviewText:
Recently tried this coffee as I’m a coffee lover and have many Nescafé products yet find this definitely to the connoisseur in me, a defined cup of Gold.
Using a frothy milk to give this a twist is ideal.
2 sugars and it’s done.
The process of turning the kettle on and preparing each part of making this is enjoyable and worth the effort.
The many different styles of this Gold should accommodate the various Gold Rush drinkers in us all.
Results.Title: Strong coffee to get you going in the morning.

Results.ReviewText:
I have always enjoyed this dark blend of coffee, very full flavoured , wonderful aroma and great anytime of day. The jar contains over 100 servings and the last is as good as the first! The quality of the coffee is not diminished once opened. I take a jar to work and virtually all my colleagues will ask for a spoonful! Just as well it does hold so many servings!! 
I wholeheartedly recommend this coffee to any coffee lovers!
Results.Title: Perfect Everytime!
